This paper is about improving the skip-thought model, which is a popular method for learning sentence representations. The paper proposes several techniques to trim and improve the model, and evaluates it on various supervised tasks related to natural language processing. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which focuses on the intersection of computer science and linguistics. Other likely sub-categories include cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and cs.CV (Computer Vision), as these fields are closely related to natural language processing and deep learning.
